4 (c) Regardless of the pendency of any request for a fuel cost charge
5 by any electric utility, the books and records pertaining to the cost of
6 fuel of all public, municipally owned, or cooperatively owned utilities
7 that generate electricity shall be examined by the utility consumer
8 counselor not less often than quarterly, and the books and records of all
9 electric nongenerating public, municipally owned, or cooperatively
